				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I don't think that the actual rotation is the slow part, since a lot of it could be sped up with look up tables (for example a table indicating the coordinates of the pixel to use for each position at all needed angles), it's the pixel manipulation that's a killer, at least in the NES. I think that dynamic sprite rotation is out of the question for actual games on the NES... If anyone really needs it, better pre-render the sprites at the needed angles.
<br />
<br />On the SNES it might be possible for a few sprites at a time I think, but I don't know enough about it to make more specific comments.</div>

