					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I tried it earlier on the year, and I managed to pixel rotate a little 8x8 sprite, but I also tried a 16x16 sprite and it caused lagging.  Since I was planning on rotating big sprites, I tried to find a way to divide the work of rotating sprites between frames, but it got pretty complicated and I gave up.
<br />
<br />Now I'm just using a combination of prerendered sprites, and metasprite placement + dynamic tile scrolling tricks.  If my game takes up too much memory, I might use the cpu to rotate sprites at 90 degree angles.</div>

