				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">A common bottleneck in a lot of early computers when it comes to cpu pixel manipulation is lack of 8-bit packed pixel mode.  Most computers used nibbles to defined colors, or even worse used planar format.
<br />
<br />Maybe 4-bit packed pixel mode isn't that bad, since you can do dual-pixel rotation, but too much of that would get pretty obvious if you rotate to far either direction.</div>

